RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPEEDY JOHNY was unhurried to trail the field outside at the half, circled four wide around horses with three furlongs from the finish, loomed the threat six wide straightening out for the drive and wore down the leader through the stretch to edge away late while not switching leads to the finish. T'PRING was content to track the leader outside in the early going, started to reel in the loose frontrunner midway on the turn, assumed command at the furlong marker but could not find more to hold off the winner in deep stretch. ONANDONANDON broke in at the start, tracked the quick pacesetter in the second flight with horses on either side with five eighths left to run, was in tight between foes at the quarter pole, pushed her way through turning for home and ran on willingly through the stretch capturing third money. SANDY GRACE was allowed to settle seeing most of the field down the backside, started to gain momentum picking up rivals inside with three eighths to go, moved out seven wide for the drive and showed good late energy to the wire to get up for a minor role in the end. WHISPER ME A SONG hopped at the break, stalked near the rear three wide with a half mile remaining, put in a brief rally until the quarter pole and stalled in mid stretch. GENTLE SEAS travelled in the middle of the pack on the rail early on, offered a mild turn of foot on the rail advancing on the turn and was one paced running to the wire down the stretch. MOET MONET was hustle to the front, opened up on challengers down the back straight, began to shorten stride with a quarter left to run and stopped in mid stretch. SPIRIT O'TIPPERARY tracked the loose frontrunner inside at the half, was urged for more run on the rail midway on the turn and was empty in the four path in upper stretch. RUSHING THE SKY settled in midfield three wide outside runners down the backside, was roused between rivals into the turn, offered little response and was not a factor in the drive to the wire. FANG MEIN LIED stalked in midpack between runners down the backstretch, was asked for more run with three eighths to go, could not keep up with horses through the turn and was not involved in the stretch drive.

BEQUIA broke inwards bumping fellow rival at the break, kept a close eye on the frontrunner in the first turn, was content watching the pacesetter down the back straight, pounced to the lead outside at the quarter marker and determinedly ran to the wire but was just outfinished by the winner in deep stretch. SWEET NOLA was unhurried three wide outside near the back in the early going, settled outside runners three deep down the backside, could not find more more when roused three eighths from home and gave way on the far turn. FOXY DIVA was off a step slow to begin, trailing into the first turn, could still see the field stalking between foes down the backstretch, offered a mild run three furlongs from the finish and could not make any impact through the stretch. TRICK AND TREAT tracked between horses in the two path going into the first turn, was on hold in midpack with horses on either side at the half, lost position trying to go with the winner at the three eighths pole and retreated inside in upper stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOURFIFTYFOUR pressed inside the early leader but off the fence under a tight hold, settled down and eased back off the leading pair passing the seven-sixteenths, stalked in behind through the turn, found room inside at the top of the stretch, bid and took the lead just past the furlong marker, was just clear and held off a rallying challenger under continued urging. WAR PAINTER was urged at the break, got forward position stalking in behind the leaders about mid-pack, moved out from three to six wide on the turn fanning outside runners to be seven to eight deep in upper stretch and having gained to within striking distance, drifted a bit in the lane, surged late under stout urging but missed. HURRICANE CLAIR broke a step slowly then veered out several paths at the start, moved forward outside to get within range of the leaders going four to five wide on the turn, came out a bit in the stretch and kept on late for show. TWISTING PISTONS raced off the pace near the rail, was about mid-pack into the turn, came out a bit at the quarter pole but then cut back to the rail as a rival in front blocked the path, improved position inside. EMERANCE was ridden strongly at the start, chased from between runners, moved to the rail on the turn, came back off the rail passing the quarter pole, entered upper stretch four deep and under an all out drive, was guided back to the two path in upper- to mid-stretch and ran on but lacked the needed late kick. CHARLOTTES ROAD broke a step slowly, switched off the inside and made rapid advance between runners up the backstretch to regain contact with the main body of the field, saved ground near the rail through the turn, waited on heels briefly at the quarter pole, came out a bit at that juncture, angled out further nearing the sixteenth pole and finished up to pass horses willingly. STOLEN VALOUR moved to the fore to set the pace, faced pressure inside and out racing well off the rail, went in the three path on the turn with just outside prompted, weakened in the stretch. OLIVIA ROSE broke alertly, pressed the pace from outside four wide through the turn and under encouragement past the five-sixteenths, weakened in the stretch. THAT GIRL ARTEMUS raced outside in the back half of the field, went three to four wide on the turn and ran on evenly. MORE MONEY HUNNY tapped on the brakes racing in behind a runner early, continued inside before coming off the rail on the turn, failed to menace. CAMAROSA was fractious in the gate, broke in the air spotting the field numerous lengths, raced off the inside and was not a factor. VICTORIOUS NYQUIST lacked early speed racing off the inside, was never a threat.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 10 7F All Weather Track CR: 78. Claiming Purse 40200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Cons idered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUSKOKA GIANT was well-positioned stalking from the second flight, went four wide on the turn and was ridden along three furlongs out, put to more stout urging by the top of the stretch and with momentum, was carried out a bit in mid- and again in late-stretch, lightly brushed late and just got up. TRIGGER'S BAY moved forward inside to take the lead soon after the start, was pressured up the backstretch, moved clear coming past the three-eighths, extended the margin into upper stretch, began to shorten stride and drifted out under left-handed encouragement in mid-stretch then again late brushing a rival in the process and just failed to last. ANSELMO was outsprinted early, raced in behind runners of the second flight, moved out from four to six wide gradually on the turn while under pressure, swung out eight wide for the drive, ran on to secure show honors. IT WORKED broke a step slowly then settled into stride at the back, went three wide on the turn, was guided six wide in upper stretch, had room to run on, drifted in through middle and late stretch and finished up willingly. COLLABORATIVE stalked from between foes in the second flight, went three to four wide on the turn coming five wide into upper stretch, was carried in a bit in late stretch and ran on but needed more. STRONGER TOGETHER moved forward up the backstretch outside runners, went five then six wide on the turn and seven wide into upper stretch, needed more. NIKKI NOOTS broke a step slowly, lacked early speed, switched out racing off the inside, swung nine deep into upper stretch and passed tired rivals. QUIET SPEED broke well but soon dropped back lacking early speed while shifting in, saved ground on or just off the rail, ran on evenly. HIP TO YOUR TRICKS was lightly bumped at the break, moved forward tracking in behind the pace inside the second flight, faded. MOONQUEST got away well, prompted the pace from outside up the backstretch, began to drop back entering the turn, came up tired but was not persevered with in the final furlong. ETHNIC SOUL bobbled inwards into a rival at the start, had forward position stalking from between runners in the second flight, retreated beginning midway on the turn.
